  • Method Details

    • implement

      public void implement​(Class<?> token, Path root) throws ImplerException
      Description copied from interface: Impler
      Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

      Generated class classes name should be same as classes name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code should be placed in the correct subdirectory of the specified root directory and have correct file name. For example, the implementation of the interface List should go to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java

      Specified by:
      implement in interface Impler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      root - root directory.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - if the given class cannot be generated for one of such reasons:
      • token is null
      • root is null
      • token isn't interface
      • token is private
      • writing exception

    • implementJar

      public void implementJar​(Class<?> token, Path jarFile) throws ImplerException
      Produces jar file implementing interface specified by provided token.

      Generated class full name should be same as full name of the type token with Impl suffix added.

      During implementation creates temporary folder to store temporary .java and .class files.

      Specified by:
      implementJar in interface JarImpler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      jarFile - target .jar file.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - if the given class cannot be generated for one of such reasons:
      • Some arguments are null
      • Error occurs during implementation via implement(Class, Path)
      • JavaCompiler failed to compile implemented class
      • The problems with I/O occurred during implementation.

    • main

      public static void main​(String[] args)
      This function is used to choose which way of implementation to execute. Runs Implementor in two possible ways:
      • 2 arguments: className rootPat - runs implement(Class, Path) with given arguments
      • 3 arguments: -jar className jarPath - runs implementJar(Class, Path) with two second arguments
      If arguments are incorrect or an error occurs during implementation returns message with information about error
      Parameters:
      args - arguments for running an application
